14/09/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Norwegian Foreign Minister Jan Petersen, the current chairman of the Council of Europe's Committee of Ministers, kicked off a visit to the Western Balkans on Monday (13 September). 
In Sarajevo, he met with Bosnian counterpart, Mladen Ivanic, to discuss the country's progress and challenges related to the Euro-Atlantic integration process. 
Petersen visits Belgrade and Pristina on Tuesday.
In other news, Norwegian Prime Minister Kjell Magne Bondevik is visiting Romania. 
Meeting on Monday with counterpart Adrian Nastase, Bondevik stressed his country's support for Romania's EU accession bid and pledged to encourage Norwegian investment in Romania. 
(CoE Web site, FENA, PBS BiH, Rompres - 13/09/04)
